  "prompt": "The income paid/credited showing on my 26AS statement is Rs. 1,25,367.44 (salary income) and on Form 16, the total income shown is Rs 1,33,209 (after deducting PF). Which one should I show in ITR 1 under 'Income from Chargeable Salaries'?",
  "response": "In your situation, it is essential to report the total income accurately in your Income Tax Return (ITR). Given the figures you provided:\n\n- **26AS Statement** shows salary income of Rs. 1,25,367.44.\n- **Form 16** shows salary income of Rs. 1,33,209 (after deducting PF).\n\nYou should report the income as per Form 16 in your ITR. Form 16 is issued by your employer and is considered a more authoritative source of income because it reflects all components of your salary, including taxable allowances and deductions.\n\nTherefore, you should show Rs. 1,33,209 as your 'Income from Chargeable Salaries' in ITR 1. Make sure to include any additional details or deductions that may apply according to the tax regulations.\n\nIf you notice discrepancies between the figures in your Form 16 and those in your 26AS, it's advisable to check with your employer or the relevant financial department to resolve any inconsistencies.",
